## Mandatory Session Protocol

Mnemix is enabled for this project. All agents must use it as the repo's cross-session memory layer.

1. Start substantive work with `{{mnemix.binary}} --store {{mnemix.store_path}} recall --scope {{mnemix.scope}}`
2. Search or inspect memory when recall is too broad or you need a specific prior fact
3. Create a checkpoint before risky edits, migrations, or broad generated changes
4. End substantive work by writing a durable memory entry

Record only durable `decision`, `fact`, `procedure`, `warning`, or `summary` memories that will help future sessions.
Do not store secrets, raw transcripts, noisy logs, or unverified guesses.

Use [skills/mnemix-memory/SKILL.md](skills/mnemix-memory/SKILL.md) for the full workflow,
[mnemix/MEMORY_POLICY.md](mnemix/MEMORY_POLICY.md) for recording rules, and
[mnemix/adapters/coding_agent_adapter.py](mnemix/adapters/coding_agent_adapter.py) for Python-based agent integration.

